# No em dashes

Never use the em dash character (U+2014, `—`) in:

- UI copy, i18n strings, comments shown to users, API error messages, commit messages, or PR descriptions for Echelon
- Assistant replies to the user

Use instead:

- A period and new sentence
- A comma
- A colon
- Parentheses
- A middle dot (`·`) only as a compact separator between short labels (e.g. `name · score`)

Do not substitute en dash (`–`) as a workaround when an em dash would have been used. Prefer plain punctuation.
